item.title: Ross River Virus
item.description: Structure Ross River Virus is an endemic RNA virus found predominantly in Australia, but has been discovered in other Pacific nations such as Papua New Guinea.

item.title: Ross River Virus Script
item.description: In simplistic terms, the Ross River Virus is an Alphavirus found commonly in Australia. As an RNA virus, it consists of a protein shell, viral envelope, lipid proteins, glycoproteins and a single-stranded genome.
